Low price on the Taurus Model 4510 Judge - The Taurus Judge is the revolver that can fire shotgun shells. Taurus dubbed their .410/.45LC series revolver "the Judge", due to a large number of judges expressing interest in carrying a .410 load into the courtroom.

The Judge gives you options no other self-defense handgun can offer. While it is questionable whther or not bird shot fired from the Judge would be very effective against a dangerous adversary, don't forget that the Judge is also capable of firing buckshot and the .45 Colt cartridge...a proven manstopper. More importantly, there are self-defense situations where penetration of walls and/or injury to innocent bystanders standing behind the bad guy are very real concerns.

There is also a serious concern among city dwellers, who may not necessarily be firearms enthusiasts, but want a self-defense handgun for the apartment or car. The Judge is ideally suited for tight quarters and would minimize the chances of perforating the neighbors. The remaining cylinders could be loaded with .45 Colt loads in case the situation goes downhill. And let's not forget the most practical application of the "Judge", is that of a handy snake gun...and not just those on two-legs.
